The inquiry into alleged impropriety at the Public Investment Corporation resumes on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG - The inquiry into alleged impropriety at the Public Investment Corporation resumes on Tuesday. The Johannesburg Stock Exchange was in the hot seat on Monday. READ; Hawks hunt for 'Undercover Billionaires' executives The PIC was unable to produce any documents supporting the nearly R4-billion transaction with Erin Energy, that’s what emerged at the commission. The JSE pulled out at the last minute, refusing to let the company list. When Survé testified at the inquiry, he blamed media reports for this.